@mcollina 

For finding from where goes the warning, i spend more than hour, it's because i am not PRO debugger and like me a lot and almost all of these use Fastify (yes yes, Fastify not fastest one, but balanced between performance and features, functionality).

Maybe we just add these lines and about warnings more information will we get. Would be best for both developers (Fastify developer/authors and Fastify users).

```js
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  typeof process !== 'undefined' &&
    process.on('warning', (warning) => {
      console.warning(warning.stack);
    });
}
```

Do you like this idea?
